message.datticon.plugged: That doesn't need to be plugged in
message.datticon.redstone: I tried using redstone, but it's primitive
message.leorna.plants: Could you imagine if the whole world was covered in plants?
message.leorna.nature: Embracing nature is part of the importance of life
message.leorna.lamona: Have you tried throwing Lamona? It is mighty handy for finding my way
message.leorna.zelus: Zelus won't stop looking at me
message.vatticus.feel: Can you feel the empowerment of the arcanium around you?
message.vatticus.noend: I hear there's no end to this place, there's no end to me either
message.vatticus.strength: Arcana come upon me, give me the ultimate strength!
message.vatticus.discover: I've discovered how to awake the ancient leader of the dungeon
message.general.weapons: My weapons will conquer any foe
message.general.merik: Do not buy from Captain Merik. He does not care about quality
message.general.blade: The Arcanite Blade is incredibly powerful
message.kazari.1: They call me the «Dungeon Keeper», but I prefer to be called by my real name, got it?
message.kazari.2: Most of the other guys here just feud with each other a bunch. I had to go out and tell them to stop it myself
message.kazari.3: These blocks I've made lack the unbreakable curse that the rest of the dungeon has... or not. I don't actually know what makes them unbreakable
message.kazari.4: This house? Yeah, I built it myself using materials from your world. Couldn't stand making it out of the drab blue blocks we have here
message.kazari.5: Datticon's got talent, but he squanders it on making the same furnace six times
message.kazari.6: Hitchak's kind of bland. To each their own taste, I guess
message.kazari.7: The miniature statue men also drop keys. Good luck finding them consistently, though
message.kazari.8: You're not the first visitor we've had from your world - and I doubt you'll be the last
message.zelus.fine: Have you seen Leorna lately? She's looking mighty fine as far as I can tell
message.zelus.minions: My minions will overrun any world
message.zelus.flower: I'm thinking of giving Leorna a flower, she won't find it too fancy though
message.zelus.plants: I've always wondered, does Leorna like plants because she almost is one?
message.hunger.closer: Can you come a little closer?
message.hunger.fatten: You need to fatten yourself up
message.hunger.dinner: Let's go out to dinner; you'll be cooking

message.mysterious_man_layer_2.4: The gods are using your dreams as a battlefield
message.mysterious_man_layer_3.1: Infuse this. I can feel the strength when you do
message.mysterious_man_layer_3.2: Thank you for aiding me in my plan
message.mysterious_man_layer_3.3: The surface is just above us
message.mysterious_man_layer_3.4: Can you believe that we're submerged so far?
message.crypt_keeper.3: Take this reward, use it wisely
message.crypt_keeper.4: What the future holds is dark
message.temple_guardian.1: You are moving upwards, beware of the imminent danger
message.temple_guardian.3: This is dangerous, what are you doing here?
message.temple_guardian.5: They are getting closer to killing you
message.karos.game: So you came to play a game?
message.karos.explosion: I heard you like explosions! Hahaha
message.karos.doom: I'm here for you to meet your doom!
message.karos.cmon: C'mon c'mon get me, try your best!
message.karos.weak: You can't kill me! You weak excuse for a human
message.quadro.enough: Enough of you! You don't deserve my kill!
message.quadro.next: Looks like I'm done with this. You're next!
message.quadro.deserve: You don't deserve to be near a guardian of Arksiane!
message.raglok.dare: You dare wake me from my slumber?!
message.raglok.think: You think you can fight me?
message.raglok.great: I am the great guardian of Heliosis!
message.raglok.kill: Kill this human, kill it today!
message.raglok.compare: You're nothing compared to me! Nothing!
message.wreck.run: You should run while you still have the chance to live
message.wreck.smell: I do love the smell of death!
message.wreck.pull: Come feel the soul of Arksiane
message.wreck.freeze: Stop at once in the name of the great Arksiane!
jeicompat.tile.raw_arcanium.information: Raw Arcanium spawns in the Dungeon of Arcana, usually behind locked doors.
book.divinerpg.landing_text: This guide book is still WIP but will contain the most frequently asked questions as well as some general good knowledge about how to play the mod.
As with all mods, you have to start somewhere
book.divinerpg.entry.getting_started.ore: This chapter contains some information about the ores that will spawn inside of the Overworld, the Nether and the End.
book.divinerpg.entry.getting_started.arl: Arlemite ore usually spawns below y=70 inside of the Overworld. Arlemite ore is more common at lower heights.
book.divinerpg.entry.getting_started.rea: Realmite ore is the most common of the DivineRPG ore and usually spawns below y=52 inside of the Overworld.
book.divinerpg.entry.getting_started.rup: Rupee ore usually spawns below y=64 inside of the Overworld. Rupee ore is more common at lower heights.
book.divinerpg.entry.getting_started.blo: Bloodgem ore spawns all throughout the Nether.
book.divinerpg.entry.getting_started.tor: Torridite ore spawns all throughout the Nether. Torridite was previously known as Netherite!
book.divinerpg.entry.getting_started.the: The Watcher is a boss that is spawned using the Call of the Watcher inside of the Nether. It flies around and shoots fireballs that explode and can break the environment. The Watcher is one of a 3 mobs that drop the divine shards
book.divinerpg.entry.getting_started.anc: The Ancient Entity is a large boss that is spawned by using the Mysterious Clock. The Ancient Entity can launch the player into the air. It is one of the three boss mobs that drop divine shards
book.divinerpg.entry.getting_started.kin: The King of Scorchers is a boss that is spawned by using the Infernal Flame. It shoots fireballs fastly at the player. They drop soulfire stones as well as fury fire
book.divinerpg.entry.getting_started.aye: The Ayeraco Horde has 6 mini-bosses that can only be summoned in the end using the horde horn. The red Ayeraco will heal the other Ayeraco when its health is half. The Green Ayeraco makes the other Ayeraco immune to arrows below half health. The Blue Ayeraco speeds up the others while below half health.
The Yellow Ayeraco increases the other Ayeraco damage and finally the Purple Ayeraco will teleport the other Ayeraco at half health. This is the third and final mob that drops divine shards
book.divinerpg.entry.getting_started.enc: Rive when applied to a mining tool will excavate in a (3 x 3 x enchant level) sized radius.
Aftershock has a chance to double the damage done by melee weapons.
book.divinerpg.entry.getting_started.jac: The Jack o'Man offers the Skeleman armor, the Jack o'Man armor, the Wither Reaper armor and lastly the scythe
book.divinerpg.entry.getting_started.liv: The Livestock Merchant offers the following pets as trades: Ehu, Husk, Stone Golem, Smelter, Snapper, White Grizzle and lastly the Brown Grizzle
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.portals.1: Twilight portals are structures for traveling between the twilight dimensions and the Overworld. All twilight portals are created with at least 10 respective portal blocks in the shape of a nether portal. The four corners of the frame are not required, but portals created by the game always include them, resulting in 4 free/extra portal blocks.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.portals.2: In order to ignite the portal you need to use the twilight clock on the bottom of the portal. Twilight portals can be activated only in the Overworld or their respective dimension.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.eden_porta: An eden portal is built of divine rock. Divine shards can be obtained from: an $(l:divinerpg:getting_started/bosses#entity)ancient entity$(/l), $(l:divinerpg:getting_started/bosses#watcher)the Watcher$(/l), and the $(l:divinerpg:getting_started/bosses#ayeraco)Ayeraco$(/l) horde.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.wildwood_p: A wildwood portal is built of eden block. Souls and fragments can be collected while exploring the Eden dimension, and hearts are dropped from the $(l:divinerpg:twilight/twilight_bosses#sunstorm)Sunstorm$(/l).
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.apalachia_: An apalachia portal is built of wildwood block. Souls and fragments can be collected while exploring the Wildwood dimension, and hearts are dropped from the $(l:divinerpg:twilight/twilight_bosses#termasect)Termasect$(/l).
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.skythern_p: A skythern portal is built of eden block. Souls and fragments can be collected while exploring the Apalachia dimension, and hearts are dropped from an $(l:divinerpg:twilight/twilight_bosses#archer)eternal archer$(/l).
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.mortum_por: A mortum portal is built of eden block. Souls and fragments can be collected while exploring the Skythern dimension, and hearts are dropped from an $(l:divinerpg:twilight/twilight_bosses#cori)experienced cori$(/l).
book.divinerpg.entry.iceika.iceika_porta: An iceika portal is created using a minimum of 10 snow blocks in the shape of a nether portal. In order to ignite the portal you need to use the snow globe on the bottom of the portal.
Iceika portals can be activated only in the Overworld or the Iceika.
book.divinerpg.entry.arcana.arcana_porta: An arcana portal is created using 12 arcana portal frames in the shape of an end portal. To activate, the frames must be oriented correctly; the front face of each block must be pointed inward toward the 3×3 portal area.
Activating the portal destroys $(l)any$() blocks located in the center 3×3 square.
book.divinerpg.entry.vethea.nightmare_be: The nightmare bed must be placed in darkness to transfer the player to the vethea dimension. The player will have their inventory swapped because once you enter Vethea you are in a dream. The Overworld inventory gets restored when leaving Vethea.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.sunstorm: Sunstorm dungeons spawn inside Eden and require a eden chunk to activate.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.termasect: Termasect nests spawn inside Wildwood and require a wildwood chunk to activate.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.eternal_ar: Eternal Archer dungeons spawn inside Apalachia and require a apalachia chunk to activate.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.experience: Experienced Cori dungeons spawn inside Skythern and require a skythern chunk to activate.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.densos: Densos is a melee boss. He deals roughly 31 damage and has 500 hearts of health. Densos' best friend is Reyvor!
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.karot: Karot is basically a large angry glinthop that spawns smaller angry glinthops as minions. Karot has 625 hearts of health attacks with melee.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.reyvor: Reyvor is a ranged boss. He deals roughly 40 damage and has 500 hearts of health. Reyvor's best friend is Densos!
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.soul_fiend: Soul Fiend will give you multiple negative effects and attacks with melee. it has 550 hearts of health and deals 34 damage.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.twilight_d: Twilight demon has both melee and ranged attacks, its ranged attack will give you negative effects. It has 800 hearts of health.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.vamacheron: Vamacheron is a fast melee boss and has 675 hearts of health. Due to his speed he hits like a truck!
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.eden_ore: Eden ore spawns at all heights inside the Eden dimension, however it is very rare.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.wildwood_o: Wildwood ore spawns at all heights inside the Wildwood dimension, however it is very rare.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.apalachia_: Apalachia ore spawns at all heights inside the Apalachia dimension, however it is very rare.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.skythern_o: Skythern ore spawns at all heights inside the Skythern dimension, however it is very rare.
book.divinerpg.entry.twilight.mortum_ore: Mortum ore spawns at all heights inside the Mortum dimension, however it is very rare.
book.divinerpg.entry.iceika.structures.1: Iceika has multiple structures that spawn. Some of these different structures contain two mobs, the Workshop Tinkerer and the Workshop Merchant. Within the other structures, there are a few Tile Entities. The coalstone furnace does not require any fuel to smelt but it is slightly slower than a regular furnace.
book.divinerpg.entry.iceika.structures.2: The tile entities contain frosted chests which contain loot, this loot contains snowflakes, ice shards, snow cones, chocolate logs, peppermints, egg nog, fruit cake, sound of carols, icicle bane and the seng fur armor.
book.divinerpg.entry.arcana.dramix: Dramix is a boss with 2500 hearts of health, he is 3 blocks tall and he can go invisible. His attacks are melee however he hits like a truck. Dramix is spawned by right clicking a Wizard's Book on a Dramix Altar
book.divinerpg.entry.arcana.parasecta: Parasecta is a flying boss. Parasecta will fly around a player and hit them, it is recommended you find a way to negate knockback. Parasecta can be spawned by right clicking a Wizard's Book on a Parasecta Altar
book.divinerpg.entry.arcana.captain_meri: Captain Merik offers many trades. These trades include: Storm Sword, Ghostbane, Shadow Saber, Arcanium Saber, Captain's Sparkler, Firefly, Merik's Missile, Livicia Sword, La Vekor, Grenade and the Korma armor set
book.divinerpg.entry.arcana.datticon: Datticon offers many trades. These trades include: Star Bridge, Arcanite Tubes, Arcanite Ladder, Molten Furnace, Greenlight Furnace, Oceanfire Furnace, Moonlight Furnace, Whitefire Furnace, Demon Furnace, Elevantium, Acceleron and the Korma armor set
book.divinerpg.entry.arcana.kazari: Kazari offers many trades. These trades include: Ancient Key, Degraded Key, Soul Key, Sludge Key, Ancient Bricks, Ancient Stone, Ancient Tile, Arcanium Metal, Arcanium Power, Degraded Bricks, Dungeon Lamp, Soul Sludge and Soul Stone
book.divinerpg.entry.arcana.leorna: Leorna offers many trades. These trades include: Eucalyptus Root Seeds, Marsine Seeds, Firestock Seeds, Pinfly Seeds, Aquamarine Seeds, Hitchak Seeds, Veilo Seeds, Lamona Seeds, Arcanite Dirt and Arcanite Grass
book.divinerpg.entry.arcana.lord_vatticu: Lord Vatticus offers many trades. These trades include: Blue Dye, Experience Bottles, Soul Sand, Weak Arcana Potion, Strong Arcana Potion, Blaze Rod, Nether Wart, Wizard's Book and Enchanting Table
book.divinerpg.entry.arcana.war_general: War General offers many trades. These trades include: Meteor Mash. Starlight, Staff of Starlight, Arcanite Blaster, Arcanite Blade, General's Staff and the Vemos armor set
book.divinerpg.entry.arcana.zelus: Zelus offers a few trades. These trades include: Fyracryx Egg, Seimer Egg, Paratiku Egg and lastly Golem of Rejuvenation Egg
book.divinerpg.entry.vethea.the_hunger: The hunger spawns in the ceiling huts and is the only source of food and early vethea weapons and armor
book.divinerpg.entry.vethea.mysterious_m: Mysterious Man and Crypt Keeper are the primary source of lumps
book.divinerpg.entry.vethea.infusion_tab: The infusion table is how you're going to craft the majority of your tools. The Teaker Hammer is a great place to start. The way to use the infusion table is placing a template in the bottom slot and the correct amount of lumps in the top slot.
book.divinerpg.entry.vethea.exit_level1: To get to the second layer you can do a few things, you could mine a staircase into the pillars, you could also make a staircase out of dream dirt. There is one other way, but lets not get into why nerd poling is bad.
book.divinerpg.entry.vethea.hive: The Hive queen is a boss that drops a decent quantity of Cermile lumps.
book.divinerpg.entry.vethea.pyramid: The large pyramid structures that spawn are temples, they contain a lot of decent loot however, proceed with caution because they are very maze like and have a lot of minion mobs inside.
book.divinerpg.entry.vethea.quadrotic_al: The Quadrotic Altar is activated with dream flint. Once active the Quadro will spawn. The Quadro has 4 attacks, the first being a quick but weak melee attack, the second being a stronger melee, third being a weak rapid fire arrow and lastly a slower but stronger ranged attack!
book.divinerpg.entry.vethea.karos_altar: The Karos Altar is activated with dream flint. Once active Dr. Karos will spawn. The Dr.'s main attack is raining exploding red balls. The Dr also shoots Karos Arrows from the cannons in the walls!
book.divinerpg.entry.vethea.lunic_altar: The Lunic Altar is activated with a moon clock. Once active Lady Luna will spawn. Lady luna has 3 forms: Melee (red), Arcana (blue) and Ranged (green). Each form means she can only take that sort of damage.
book.divinerpg.entry.vethea.raglok_altar: The Raglok Altar is activated with dream flint. Raglok Gog'dure can smite you, it can blind you, it can drop heavy particles on you and lastly it can slow you down and push you very far.
effect.divinerpg.heavy_air.description: Dungeons inside Vethea contain heavy air and require dissipating before you can loot the dungeons.
